description: Gateway Classic Cars of Houston is proud to offer this stunning 1974 Dodge Dart. 1974 was a year that brought more sales to this smaller muscle car with the Arab Oil embargo. You can say it was a pretty sought after car for its time. But don't let its stature fool you this one packs a punch. Under the hood of this bad boy is a numbers matching 318 CID V8 pushing out about 230HP which was a pretty decent for its time for this smaller car. Its then strapped up to a smooth shifting 3 speed automatic transmission. The 74 Dart was redesigned to be a much more comfort oriented car, and this example is no exception with a comfortable ride, and easy steering inputs. Some of the amenities that add to the drivability of this car are AC, CD Player, Power Brakes, Power Steering, Seat Belt, Vinyl Interior and radial tires. To see HD pictures and videos of this 1937 Ford Pickup, please visit GatewayClassicCars.com. description: For sale in our St. Louis showroom is a Top Banana 1973 Dodge Challenger. The odometer reads 63,836, which is believed to be the actual mileage on the car. Options for this 1973 Dodge Challenger include: AM Radio, Power Brakes, Seat Belts, Vinyl Interior, and Raised White Letter Radial Tires. Powering this 1973 Dodge Challenger is a 340 CID 4BBL V8 with an Edlebrock aluminum intake, and is believed to be the original engine to the car. High Performance, stock exhaust manifolds flow to the newer exhaust and produce an awesome sound. A 727 TorqueFlite automatic transmission transfers the power to the 8 3/4 rear end. This 73' Challenger is finished in Top Banana exterior paint with a black vinyl top and black decals on each door. Both the yellow paint, vinyl top, and decals are in good condition, and produce the classic Mopar look. The original black vinyl interior is also in good condition, free from rips, tears, and major wear. The pistol grip, slap stick shifter provides an awesome, nostalgic look and feel to the Challenger. This Challenger features fender turn signals, which was a rare option for the Challenger in 1973. The Challenger is one of the very few muscle cars from the end of the muscle car era, 1972-1975, that have stood the test of time and are still desired today. To view this eye catching 1973 Dodge Challenger in greater detail including HD pictures and an HD video, visit www.GatewayClassicCars.com or our St. Louis showroom. For more information please call 618-271-3000 or email STL@GatewayClassicCars.comThe good ones go fast, call now for availability!

description: 1973 Dodge Challenger Ralleye edition - Only 43k miles!! Car was kept inside under cover since 1973! Has a new bright red paint job on it - virtually no rust. Clean & straight.... Interior is impeccable! Has a 318 LA V8 - has been modified to increase horsepower by over a 120 horsepower. (new cam, headers, fuel pump, 4bbl carb, dual radiator, etc.) New chrome rims & racing tires. New battery. Air shocks. Lots of chrome under the hood. If you are a Mopar guy like me & want a challenger that looks like the 70/71's (but don't have 80k in your wallet) - this car is perfect. The Dodge Challenger did not change much from 70 - 74 when production ended at least on the interior / exterior - the only changes generally were the engines. This modified 318 is equivalent to the mopar 360 v8 engine output. This really is a good car - don't miss this opportunity to own an American Muscle car Icon! It looks great & sounds like there's a TRex under the hood when it rumbles!
